        <h2 id="what-is">What is Nightwatch?</h2>
        <p>Nightwatch is a Slovenia-based SEO rank tracker founded in 2016. It carved out a niche between hobby trackers (SerpWatch, ProRankTracker) and enterprise platforms (AccuRanker, STAT) by pairing professional-grade tracking with agency-friendly white-label reports at a price small agencies could justify.</p>

        <p>The core product does five things:</p>

        <ol>
          <li><strong>Rank tracking</strong> — daily keyword position updates across Google, Maps, YouTube, Amazon, and Bing</li>
          <li><strong>Hyper-local tracking</strong> — position tracking down to ZIP code and physical address</li>
          <li><strong>SERP feature monitoring</strong> — featured snippets, PAA, image packs, AI Overviews</li>
          <li><strong>White-label reports</strong> — fully branded PDF and live-dashboard reports for clients</li>
          <li><strong>Site audit</strong> — a lightweight technical SEO crawler for client hygiene reports</li>
        </ol>

        <p>What Nightwatch is <em>not</em>: a backlink tool, a content optimizer, a GBP management platform, or a publishing tool. It tracks. Anything else is on you.</p>

        <h2 id="features">Nightwatch features — the full 2026 walkthrough</h2>
        <p>Here is what actually matters in daily agency use.</p>

        <h3>1. Visual rank tracker</h3>
        <p>The dashboard is genuinely the cleanest in the category — clear position graphs, visibility scores per project, and a side-by-side competitor view that updates daily. Drag-and-drop dashboards let you build custom views per client without engineering help.</p>

        <h3>2. Hyper-local + Map Pack tracking</h3>
        <p>Nightwatch tracks Map Pack positions for any address you specify, down to ZIP code. This is unusual at $39/mo — most competitors gate this behind enterprise tiers. For multi-location service businesses, this alone justifies the subscription.</p>

        <h3>3. SERP-feature monitoring</h3>
        <p>Tracks featured snippets, People Also Ask, image packs, Knowledge Panel presence, and AI Overviews (where they appear). Good for spotting opportunities to win SERP real estate beyond the blue links.</p>

        <h3>4. White-label client reports</h3>
        <p>PDF exports and live dashboard URLs, fully branded with your logo, colors, and custom domain. Standard plan and above. The single biggest reason agencies pick Nightwatch over a cheaper alternative.</p>

        <h3>5. Built-in site audit</h3>
        <p>A lightweight crawler for technical hygiene: broken links, meta-tag issues, status-code problems, and basic Core Web Vitals. Useful for client reports; not deep enough to replace Ahrefs Site Audit or Screaming Frog.</p>

        <h2 id="pricing">Nightwatch pricing — what it really costs in 2026</h2>
        <p>Sticker price first, then the real total cost of running an SEO program around it.</p>

        <div class="table-wrap">
